      "content": "it doesn't feel like a survivor thing. it feels like i'm just watching my life burn down and i'm the one who lit the match. everyone looks at me and they don't see me, they just see the debt and the failure. i feel like if i stayed, i'd just keep dragging them down with me. like the only way to actually stop being a burden and stop the shame is to just... not be a part of it anymore. to just stop existing so they can move on without me.",
